section.section:
The Commission consists of seven members appointed by the Governor. No more than three members of the Commission may be individuals admitted to practice law in this State. In nominating and appointing members, special consideration shall be given to individuals who have knowledge of compensation practices and financial matters. The Governor shall appoint:
Two members from a list of the names of at least five nominees submitted by the President of the Senate;
Two from a list of the names of at least five nominees submitted by the Speaker of the House of Delegates;
One from a list of the names of at least three nominees submitted by the Maryland State Bar Association, Inc.; and
Two at large.
